title: Mint more puzzle access tokens?
body:
Prior to the $COIN launch we sold 20 Puzzle Access NFTs on OpenSea to help seed the COIN/ETH pair on Uniswap. 

Uniswap: https://uniswap.info/pair/0xcce852e473ecfdebfd6d3fd5bae9e964fd2a3fa7

Previously Sold Puzzle NFTs on OpenSea: https://opensea.io/assets?search=%7B%22query%22%3A%22coin%27s%20e-den%20cosplay%22%7D

We have received some requests to mint more NFTs that will allow more players to submit the final solution to our new puzzle which unlocks on Thursday. 
Countdown here: https://countingdownto.com/?c=3196834#.X1OYgVJy3oo.

The puzzle is designed in a way where the final step requires that you prove that you own on these puzzle NFTs in order to claim the prize, which is $30,470 COIN, currently equivalent to about $15,000 USD. 

We could list $15,000 USD worth of NFTs to facilitate more players and also to buy the $COIN off the market in case the winner chooses to dump all of their winnings. 

Even if we minted these tokens, there is no guarantee that they would sell out. However, the prize is enticing and these could be available throughout the puzzle until they are sold out. 

Remember you will need to be in the Coin's E-Den private discord chat in order to participate on the puzzle trail. Details on how to join are here: https://medium.com/@coin_artist_17801/coin-launch-9e53bf27c095

TLDR; Should we mint more puzzle access tokens (NFTs)?
author: 0x148e2ED011A9EAAa200795F62889D68153EEacdE
